			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Fixing their spell lineup would be fine, but improving Kindle is also a necessity to make them worthwhile.  Their sustained DPS needs to be around that of the water pet... or a little higher due to their excessive "situational" usefulness thanks to mob resists.  Going oom makes them suck, and it takes maybe two typical xp mob fights... tops.
<br />

<br />
I'll be more specific than the above poster on the spell lineup change... just <span style="font-style: italic">remove Root</span>, and most mages will be happier.  Dispel is no longer a problem since the dispel changes a few patches ago.
<br />

<br />
These are minor minor changes.  It doesn't take long to figure out the sustained DPS of 50 mana/tick (or whatever is appropriate) at whatever their best ratio DD is, to make sure that their DPM is close to the water pet.  Hopefully it wouldn't take long to remove root from their spell lineup.
<br />

<br />
This change will make a LOT of mages happy, without giving them some new advantage or improved abilities.  It gives them back some variety in their game that they've been missing for a long while.<br />_________________<br />Arhallia Ironborne
