				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Arhallia wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Fixing their spell lineup would be fine, but improving Kindle is also a necessity to make them worthwhile.  Their sustained DPS needs to be around that of the water pet... or a little higher due to their excessive "situational" usefulness thanks to mob resists.  Going oom makes them suck, and it takes maybe two typical xp mob fights... tops.
<br />
</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
My view of the pets are different.  I think they should be this way.
<br />

<br />
Use the Air Pet as base.  It is fairly good, just needs to scale better with focus, especially DPS.  
<br />

<br />
Earth pet twice as good as air pet at tanking, only half the DPS.  This is the pet you want when Tanking.
<br />

<br />
Water pet half as good as air pet at tanking, twice the DPS in melee/procs.  This is the pet you use for sustained/melee DPS.
<br />

<br />
Fire pet 1/3 as good as the air pet at tanking, but 4x the DPS of the air pet for 2 minutes then drops to 1/2 the DPS of the air pet. And get rid of all AE spells.  They are just too dangerous.   This pet should only follow the caster around.  It should only melee if mob moves into its range.  It should auto sit if out of mana.  This is the pet you use for ranged/staggered pull camps.  
<br />

<br />
Make the differences between the pets more pronucned.  Give us a reason to change pets between battles.  
<br />

<br />
Currently, there is not a big enough difference between the pets to make you switch them if you already have one out and buffed. 
<br />

<br />
Just my 2cp.<br />_________________<br />Dabrighter Blazemeister
