				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I totally agree with you Arhallia, fire pets need to be fixed. Personally I would be more than happy if they could get rid of the wizard style and return the fire pet to warrior class again. I have posted my vision of what the 50+ fire pets should be a few times, but I will be glad to do it again <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="icon_smile" border="0" />
<br />

<br />
- Fire pet = warrior type.
<br />

<br />
- Get the FireElementalAura back!
<br />

<br />
- Damage of the fire pet should come from melee and an upgrade to the fire nuke the pre-50 fire pets had, basically I want it to have about same damage a water pet can reach: fire pet melee + improved fire nuke should equal water pet melee + water pet backstab + water pet nuke.
<br />

<br />
- Let it have the lowest hp. This would offset the fact that it would be easier to use than the water pet (where resists allow it) and that it has a strong, built-in DS. This pet could also be a serious upgrade to the epic pet!
<br />

<br />

<br />
The improved nuke should of course NOT depend on mana anymore. A mana based pet is just ridiculous, pets are the sustained damage part of a magicians arsenal!<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=423546" target="_blank" class="postlink">Izudin</a>, 65 Arch Convoker on Quellious</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
