				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Now forgive me if I'm one of the many people who seem to be misunderstanding you, Izudin, but the fire pet you describe has:
<br />

<br />
-low hp (lower than or equal to water pet)
<br />
-high DS
<br />
-better DD proc than water pet
<br />
-no backstab
<br />
-equal DPS output of water pet, except mostly from procs
<br />

<br />
Now, what we are trying to tell you is:
<br />

<br />
-ALL fire pets (including Child of Ro) have always had FireElementalAura.  It's just rare for them to cast it on themselves after level 50, mainly because they aren't intended to be tanks.
<br />
-Giving the fire pet a high DS, even if you gave it the same hp as the water pet, would mean absolutely nothing.  That pet wouldn't last 2 rounds in a battle with a planar or GoD mob, therefore making the DS completely obsolete, especially since you have already told us this pet isn't meant to tank.  So why keep it?  Because of sentimental value? Please...
<br />
-If you made the fire pet have equal DPS output of water pet, no one would use water pet anymore.  Then wouldn't we be in the same boat we are now, except with a different pet?  And contrary to popular belief, not very many mobs have insane FR, especially in PoP.  Our best two PoP nukes are fire-based, after all.
<br />
-Fire pets tanked like they did before because they could actually live for awhile against older generation mobs.  Nowadays, even if you had a direct upgrade to the old fire pet, it wouldn't stand a chance.
<br />
-People seem to LIKE the new roles pets have.  I know I do.  Why mess with it if all they need to do is remove root/dispell, and up the mana regen on Kindle?  It just doesn't make sense to create an entirely new fire pet if the current one only needs a couple fixes.
<br />

<br />
As for my own personal opinion, I believe the fire pet was originally intended as a raid pet, and therefore I don't think removing its AE nuke is completely necessary.  However, I won't argue that it is very dangerous to have a pet that uses an AE nuke, especially when none of our other pets has any kind of AE damage ability.  I also won't argue that sometimes, AE's just come in handy.  One solution would be to make a separate fire pet spell (see Rage of Xomm/Dyzil's Deafening Decoy) that only casts AE nukes.  Call it our "crowd-control-slash-mass-genocide" pet.<br />_________________<br />--<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=559376" target="_blank" class="postlink">Arc</a>--
