			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">From another post i made <a href="http://forum.magecompendium.com/viewtopic.php?t=15424" target="_blank" class="postlink">http://forum.magecompendium.com/viewtopic.php?t=15424</a>
<br />

<br />
 think that the opinion of most mages around the tower here is that the fire pet sucks. I also think the opinion of most mages is that a beefier servant of ro-style pet would be a good alternative. The perma-rooting and moving issue always came up as a problem for coding, i think i know how to get around this. 
<br />

<br />
The pet would cast a spell at a 6 second interval, something like 
<br />

<br />
Blast of Ro 
<br />
Decrease hp by 600 
<br />
resist -50 or -100, chromatic or prismatic 
<br />
range 200 
<br />
AUTOCAST: Bind of Ro 
<br />

<br />
Bind of ro 
<br />
Root 
<br />
Duration: 12seconds (maybe 18) 
<br />
Unresistable 
<br />
Target: self 
<br />

<br />
The end result of this is a 100 dps pet (600dmg/6sec), barring resists, which stays in one spot as long as it is aggroed, which doesn't require any new coding 
<br />

<br />

<br />
since each lvl of foci increases pet level by 1, the nuke scaling would be most easily done by having the damage portion of the nuke be 
<br />

<br />
decrease hitpoints by 500 (lvl 60) to 800 (lvl 65) 
<br />

<br />
numbers not exact but you get the idea. There are also a couple unknown instant damage formulas which are probably not linear like the above formula, and might better relate to the larger jump that pets take going from VT gloves to time focus. My whole focus what to make a decent change with the least amount of coding possible, so the basic linear progression would probably be the easiest, while keeping the recast the same.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
